data.text:
DOES NOT HAVE A DEMO!

YOU MUST HAVE THE CERBERUS COYOTE HEAD HEAD FOR THIS PSD KIT (check the "works with" link)

What you will get:

• PSD Shading & Texture Template for:

• Cerberus Coyote Head

•• Head, Ear PSD

••• Premade Markings for Head and Ears

• ToS Notecard

•••• Uses default eyelashes

---------------------------------------------------------------------

This template was intended as a modders resource. It can only be used for personal or commercial mods.

- You DO NOT have permission to resell this product without custom textures.

- You DO NOT have permission to resell this product without them being included in a mod kit. (Basically, do not resell these the same way you purchased them, that being this product with the texture.)

- You DO NOT have permission to give away this product to other people or alt accounts.

- You DO NOT have permission to say you created these items as your own work.

- You CAN NOT use any layers from this in any other creation but this head (This means you cannot move any layers onto any other products. They all must stay on the Coyote Head)

- You may only resell this as an avatar mod.

Any break in this ToS will result in violators being reported to Linden Labs.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

What did I just buy?

- You bought a PSD Kit. It includes basic texture(s) if you just wish to recolor whatever product you bought. However, I suggest to never do this because it will never look as good.

Where are my textures?

- Other than the basic texture already included, you must use the PSD to create your own textures.

Where are my mesh part(s)?

- There are -no- mesh parts included in the PSD Kits. They are designed for specific avatars that already exist.

If you do not already have the part for this, or don't plan on getting it, DO NOT buy this Kit.

Almost any product our kits are designed for can be found on the Marketplace with little to no effort. Just use the search function!

What does PSD mean?

- It is the type of file saved by Photoshop. You -must- have a program that can open a Photoshop file that includes folders to use this product.
